{
  "stem": "15938.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so many times people asked me, are you sorry you didn't go?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Was never sorry I didn't go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "First of all, looking back on it now, I wouldn't have survived, because they would have found me somewhere, somehow.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was too small to hide.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It wasn't like hiding in a big town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whatever went through, I think if I would have come back and survived hiding with this man and my parents would have gone to Auschwitz, I don't think I would have ever forgiven myself.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I think I'd done the right choice, whatever, because to live with that guilt, I don't think I could have lived with it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there was no question I wasn't going to go without my parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had the family together, so whatever happens, together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we got to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The train, it-- this-- it was a death plane-- train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's all huddled in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was quiet and then screaming and then crying and then, you know-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] occasionally they pushed us in with a water and-- it was-- it was-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's undescribable.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's-- you must have heard it before when people talk about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You can't describe the-- you know, you can't describe a smell and an atmosphere and-- and-- and a child who's never seen death or a body lying with a body.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, it's-- And then when we arrived, they opened the wagons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and you could see these bodies taking from all the-- from all the wagons.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you know, it's-- it's not describable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's not-- not something you can explain.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My thoughts.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's when the thoughts of hunger came into-- cold and hunger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you don't know which point in life hunger and self-preservation takes over.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
